The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, May 01, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, May 1, 2004				 																What to do this weekend				 																																	Watch A Midsummer Nights Dream staged by The Dramatics Club of St James School, in association with The Telegraph in Schools, at GD Birla Sabhagar, 6 pm on Saturday and Sunday. Tickets available at the school.				 																Soccer meet				 																																	Cheer the teams at the inter-school five-a-side football tournament, organised by The Telegraph in Schools, at CC amp;FC, on Saturday and Sunday.				 																Milestone				 																																	Be there at the opening of the 54th foundation day celebrations of the Childrens Little Theatre by Governor Viren J. Shah, at Rabindra Sadan, on Sunday at 6 pm. Abanindranath Tagores Nalak will be staged. 				 																																	Browse through Illusions, an exhibition to mark the 45th anniversary of Birla Industrial amp; Technological Museum, on its premises, that Governor Viren J. Shah will inaugurate on Sunday at 11 am.				 																																	Listen to film-maker Adoor Gopalakrishnan at the third Satyajit Ray Memorial Talk, at Satyajit Ray Film amp; Television Institute, on Sunday at 5.30 pm. Nizhalkuthu will be screened later.				 																Edu talk				 																																	Drop in for an illustrated talk on Minimally Invasive Education Project at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, at 4 pm.				 																Soiree				 																																	Enjoy an evening of classical music, hosted by Kirana Sangeet Academy, at Kala Kunj, at 6.30 pm.
